@@TJvDateTimePicker.DropDownDate
Summary
  Indicates the initial date to display when the calendar illustration is shown and
  <LINK TDateTimePicker.Date,Date> or <LINK TDateTimePicker.Time,Time> equals
  NullDate.
Description
  Use DropDownDate to specify an initial date that is shown in the drop-down calendar illustration,
  when <LINK TDateTimePicker.Date,Date> or <LINK TDateTimePicker.Time,Time> - depending on the
  <LINK TDateTimePicker.Kind,Kind> property - equals NullDate.

  For example, if <LINK TDateTimePicker.Kind,Kind> is set to dtkDate, <LINK TDateTimePicker.Date,Date>
  and NullDate are set to 1-1-2000, DropDownDate
  is set to 2-2-2002 and NullDate equals '(None)', then the text '(None)' is shown in the edit box.
  If the user drops down the calendar illustration then the date 2-2-2002 is highlighted.
