Description
  Use NullText to specify a date or time - depending on the <LINK TDateTimePicker.Kind,Kind>
  property - that represents the
  text to display when <LINK TDateTimePicker.Date,Date> or <LINK TDateTimePicker.Time,Time>
  equals NullDate. If the user entered a date or time equal to
  nulldate, thus the <LINK TDateTimePicker.Date,Date> or <LINK TDateTimePicker.Time,Time>
  property is equal to NullDate, then the string represented by NullText is displayed.
